### 13. How MDX Integration Pages Are Built

**Pipeline:**

1. **Source definition:** `fumadocs-mdx` defineCollections + source.config.ts
2. **MDX loading:** Files in `src/content/integrations/*.mdx` auto-discovered
3. **Schema validation:** IntegrationPageSchema validated at build time
4. **Runtime access:** `getIntegrationPage([slug])` returns typed page data with:
   - `data` object (frontmatter + inferred types)
   - `data.body` (MDX component tree)
   - `slugs` array
5. **Static generation:** `generateStaticParams()` in `[slug]/page.tsx` pre-renders all integrations
6. **Code generation:** `.source/server.ts` auto-maintained by fumadocs-mdx (DO NOT EDIT MANUALLY)

---

## Recommendation for 37 Upcoming Integrations

**You have three options:**

### Option A: MDX Stubs (Recommended for content flexibility)
Create 37 MDX files in `src/content/integrations/` with:
```yaml
---
title: "Sentry"
description: "Error tracking and monitoring integration."
keywords: [...]
category: "monitoring"
tagline: "Capture errors, releases, and performance."
status: "coming-soon"
ogTitle: "Sentry Integration – Coming Soon"
ogDescription: "..."
canonicalUrl: "https://lightfast.ai/integrations/sentry"
updatedAt: "2026-04-15T00:00:00Z"
---

Sentry integration coming soon. Join the waitlist to be notified when available.
```

**Pros:**
- Reuses existing rendering pipeline (fumadocs + getIntegrationPage)
- Full SEO control per integration
- Can add unique copy, FAQs, banners per integration
- Static generation works as-is
- Type-safe with IntegrationPageSchema

**Cons:**
- 37 new files to create and maintain
- Duplicate metadata across files

### Option B: TS Config + Dynamic Route (Fastest iteration)
Keep `UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS` in TS, create new dynamic route:
```typescript
// apps/www/src/app/(app)/(marketing)/(content)/integrations/coming-soon/[slug]/page.tsx

import { UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS } from "../../_lib/upcoming-integrations";

export function generateStaticParams() {
  return UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS.map((i) => ({ slug: i.id }));
}

export default function ComingSoonPage({ params }) {
  const integration = UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS.find(i => i.id === params.slug);
  // Render dynamic page from TS config
}
```

**Pros:**
- No new files to create
- Single source of truth (TS config)
- Fast to implement

**Cons:**
- SEO metadata generation is manual
- Different URL pattern (`/integrations/coming-soon/sentry` vs `/integrations/sentry`)
- Not integrated with fumadocs pipeline
- Can't leverage existing IntegrationPageSchema validation

### Option C: Convert TS to MDX (Hybrid)
Generate 37 MDX files from `UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS` array at build time or check-in time.

**Pros:**
- Scales with fumadocs
- Full SEO + content flexibility
- Single URL pattern

**Cons:**
- Build-time generation overhead or check-in script maintenance

---

## Summary Table

| Aspect | Implementation |
|--------|---|
| **Live integrations** | 3 MDX files (github, linear, vercel) in `src/content/integrations/` |
| **Frontmatter fields** | IntegrationPageSchema (title, description, keywords, providerId, tagline, category, status, faq, featuredImage, docsUrl, updatedAt, canonicalUrl, noindex, nofollow) |
| **Status support** | "live" \| "beta" \| "coming-soon" — already in schema |
| **SEO** | `emitIntegrationSeo()` generates metadata + JSON-LD from IntegrationPageData |
| **Sidebar CTA** | Shows "Join waitlist" for coming-soon, "Connect in workspace" for live/beta |
| **Fumadocs config** | `source.config.ts` + auto-maintained `.source/server.ts` |
| **Icon library** | IntegrationLogoIcons (53 icons, includes 30+ of upcoming providers) |
| **Icon mapping** | getProviderIcon() maps only 5 ProviderSlug values (apollo, github, vercel, linear, sentry) |
| **Upcoming list** | TS config UPCOMING_INTEGRATIONS (37 items, UpcomingIntegrationsList component) |

**To implement coming-soon pages at `/integrations/<slug>`, Option A (MDX stubs) is the cleanest fit for your existing pipeline.**

